CAPE Town City have confirmed the signing of Nigerian midfielder Abdul Ajagun. The former Nigeria Under-20 captain joins The Citizens from Jupiler Pro League side Kortrijk. The Cape based side confirmed the 27-year-old on their Twitter account on Friday morning. The midfielder has over 200 professional appearances and has plied his trade in the top-flight leagues of Greece, Netherlands and Belgium. "Cape Town City is delighted to announce the signing of midfielder Abdul Ajagun. The midfielder joins from Belgium Pro League side Kortrijk," the club statement read. Ajugan scored 10 goals and registered eight assists in 74 games for the Belgian top-flight side after joining them from Panathinaikos in 2017. AJAGUN ANNOUNCED ??#iamCityFC pic.twitter.com/YRRk7upabe 